And is it posiible to make a deal with a Japanese animation studio?</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#CCCCCC><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ueaglemaina.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EagleMaina</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Karbonite</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>4/14/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#1B1B37>5:33:36 am</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://pages.infinit.net/maina2/ezboard/Maina.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Animation...</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">you're right. Very few tv animation is done in the USA or in Canada. Everything is done in China now. That's kinda sad because the animation is not very good and even if there is some mistakes they won't correct it because they are payed so cheaply. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
